Week Ending Aug 29, 2025
This report provides a summary of the research produced by J.P. Morgan Global Energy Equity Research. Key highlights from the past week are below:
- APAC Energy Transition: Tightness and Tribulations: Ten Fresh Tacks on Clean Energy Supply
- ENN Energy: Model Update
- International Refining: Singapore Clean Product Inventories Fall \(\sim 2\) mmbbls w/w
- California Refining: Diesel Inventories Decline w/w, Remain Near Seasonal Lows
- Karoon Energy: Clarity at Bauna
- JPMC Utilities Daily: 28 August: DRX, RWE, ANE, EOAN
- EU Oil & Gas: Taking Stock: Key drivers and Q&A for investors; Seeking superior equity barbells of leverage and resilience
- Indian Oil Marketing Companies: Top down risks vs. bottom up earnings. Risk reward favorable
- EIA Weekly Data: Key Takeaways for Week of 8/22 Data
- JPMC Utilities Daily: 27 August: ORSTED, UK Water, RED, UK Retail, NG/, IBE, SSE
- Viva Energy: 1H25 Result - Cost-out and synergies driving C&M earnings recovery in challenging market conditions
- JPMC Utilities Daily: 26 August: ORSTED x2, US Offshore, FORTUM, ELE
- APA Group: Risk to capex timing, valuation full; Downgrade to Neutral
- ADNOC GAS: Still lots to like and longer-term guidance looks conservative but transparency could be improved
- JPM E&P Shale Well Watcher: Updated Lower 48 Supply Forecasts
- Sinopec Corp-H: New Chairman hints at potential shift in strategic direction, but earnings impact hinges on the details
- MEG Energy: 2Q25 Model Update
- Saudi Aramco: Model Update Post-2Q; Reiterate OW
- ASEAN Petrochemicals: Stocks build momentum as gov't policies push for industry repair, but is it too much too soon? Top pick - PTTGC
- Targa Resources Corp.: APAC Investor Call Takeaways: Premier Permian
See page 14 for analyst certification and important disclosures, including non- US analyst disclosures.

J.P. Morgan does and seeks to do business with companies covered in its research reports. As a result, investors should be aware that the firm may have a conflict of interest that could affect the objectivity of this report. Investors should consider this report as only a single factor in making their investment decision.
